The '''Chartered Institute of Cost and Management Accountants''' (CICMA)<ref>{{Cite web|title = Chartered Institute of Cost & Management Accountants of Nigeria|url = http://www.introschool.com/professional-centers/431|website = www.introschool.com|accessdate = 2015-10-27}}</ref> is a [[Nigeria]]n – based [[professional accounting body]] offering [[Accounting]] [[education]] and [[professional qualification]]s in [[cost]] and [[management]] [[accountancy]] and related subjects, focus on [[accounting]], [[business]] and [[government operations]]. The head office of the institute is in [[Kaduna]]. The institute also has regional offices at [[Abuja]], [[Kano]], [[Jos]] and [[Port Harcourt]]. As at September 2015, it had 8,200 members working in and outside [[Nigeria]]. It also has 4,500 registered students.

The institute is recognized by the [[Financial Reporting Council of Nigeria]]<ref>{{Cite web|title = Welcome To FRC|url = http://www.financialreportingcouncil.gov.ng|website = www.financialreportingcouncil.gov.ng|accessdate = 2015-12-25}}</ref> as it is in its institutions list for education and promotion of [[cost]] and [[management accounting]] in [[Nigeria]].

== History ==
The institute was founded in 2000, and was formally known as Institute of Cost and Management Accountants (ICMA). In the year 2002, the enabling Act establishing the institute commenced at the [[National Assembly (Nigeria)|Nigerian National Assembly]]. At the [[House of Representatives (Nigeria)|House of Representatives]], the word “Chartered” was added and the name of the institute was changed to “Chartered Institute of Cost and Management Accountants” On 25 May 2007, the Clerk of the Senate of the Federal Republic of Nigeria transmitted the CICMA Bill with other fourteen Bills to the then President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]] for his assent, but he left the office without signing any of the [[Bill (law)|Bill]]s from the [[National Assembly (Nigeria)]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = National Assembly {{!}} Federal Republic of Nigeria|url = http://nass.gov.ng/|website = nass.gov.ng|accessdate = 2015-10-28}}</ref> The Act for the establishment of the institute is still pending [[Assent procedure|Assent]] and [[Gazette]].

In May 2006, an Expert Assessor's Committee from the Federal Ministry of Education,<ref>{{Cite web|title = Home|url = http://www.education.gov.ng|website = www.education.gov.ng|accessdate = 2015-12-25}}</ref> Abuja, visited for assessment of the programmes and qualification of the institute in order to advise the Office of the Head of Service of the Federation <ref>{{Cite web|title = Office Of The Head Of The Civil Service Of The Federation - Home|url = http://www.ohcsf.gov.ng|website = www.ohcsf.gov.ng|accessdate = 2015-12-25}}</ref>(OHCSF) on the standard/rating of relevance of the professional qualifications of the institute for entry into posts in the [[Federal Civil Service Commission (Nigeria)|Federal Civil Service Commission]] <ref>{{Cite web|title = Federal Civil Service Commission of Nigeria|url = http://www.fedcivilservice.gov.ng|website = www.fedcivilservice.gov.ng|accessdate = 2015-12-25}}</ref>[[Federal Civil Service Commission (Nigeria)|(Nigeria)]]. Their report states: “Having examined the Programmes and qualifications of ICMA, the Committee observed that they compare favorably with those of similar recognized accounting Bodies. It was therefore recommended that holders of [[ICMA Pakistan|ICMA]] qualifications be placed at par with their counterparts holding qualifications of similar Accounting Bodies such as [[Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria]] <ref>{{Cite web|title = ICAN - Welcome to Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria|url = http://www.icanig.org|website = www.icanig.org|accessdate = 2015-12-25}}</ref>[[Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria|(ICAN)]] and [[Association of National Accountants of Nigeria|Association of National Accountants of Nigeria (ANAN)]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = ANAN {{!}} Association of National Accountants of Nigeria|url = http://www.anan.org.ng|website = www.anan.org.ng|accessdate = 2015-10-28}}</ref>

In June, 2006 CICMA established an offshoot known as the Association of Cost and Management Accountants.<ref>{{Cite web|title = ASSOCIATION OF COST AND MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTANTS|url = http://acma.org.ng/|website = acma.org.ng|accessdate = 2015-10-27}}</ref> In 2011, the institute was listed among approved professional bodies in Nigeria by the Financial Reporting Council of Nigeria.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Registration Information|url = http://www.financialreportingcouncil.gov.ng/index.php/registration/registration-information|website = www.financialreportingcouncil.gov.ng|accessdate = 2015-12-09|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151219163804/http://financialreportingcouncil.gov.ng/index.php/registration/registration-information#|archive-date = 2015-12-19|dead-url = yes|df = }}</ref>

==Membership and certification==
CICMA has two grades of full membership, Associate Members use the designatory letters "ACMA" and Fellow Members use the designatory letters "FCMA". To be admitted as an Associate, a candidate must have completed a period of relevant working experience and passed a series of examinations; candidates can also be admitted to membership by way of exemption or by accreditation of prior learning. To become a Fellow, a candidate must have been admitted an ACMA with five years [[post-nominal letters]].

