'''Left-hand–right-hand activity chart''' is an illustration that shows the contributions of the right and left hands of a worker and the balance of the workload between the right and left hands.<ref>Groover, M. P. (2007). ''Work Systems: The Methods, Measurement & Management of Work'', Prentice Hall, {{ISBN|978-0-13-140650-6}}</ref> The [[chart]] is very effective method to analyze the work done by a single worker and it is very helpful in improving the work done by the worker.

